{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775901384962,"sessionID":"ses_284083eaaffeJGoSkdYn83qwvG","part":{"id":"prt_d7bf8a100001oZjRZ2vAgzS8Vt","messageID":"msg_d7bf897ca001MxDpl2Thc7Hwtu","sessionID":"ses_284083eaaffeJGoSkdYn83qwvG","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775901387394,"sessionID":"ses_284083eaaffeJGoSkdYn83qwvG","part":{"id":"prt_d7bf8aa28001UA6rQvpbg9GuZQ","messageID":"msg_d7bf897ca001MxDpl2Thc7Hwtu","sessionID":"ses_284083eaaffeJGoSkdYn83qwvG","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-dc63180b00764d76a3d340498efde77f","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/sandbox-orchestration/spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/sandbox-orchestration/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Sandbox Orchestration Specification\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: Orchestrate agent sandboxes via Kubernetes CRDs (AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter), a Gin HTTP API (workload manager), session persistence, garbage collection, and optional service-account authentication.\n5: \n6: ## Requirements\n7: \n8: ### Requirement: AgentRuntime CRD schema and API registration\n9: The system SHALL expose a namespaced `AgentRuntime` custom resource in API group `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`, version `v1alpha1`, with subresource `status`, print column `Age` from `.metadata.creationTimestamp`, and SHALL register list kind `AgentRuntimeList`.\n10: \n11: #### Scenario: Group version and resource naming\n12: - **GIVEN** a Kubernetes API client resolving the CRD\n13: - **WHEN** the group, version, and kind are read from type metadata\n14: - **THEN** `GroupVersion` is `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`, kind `AgentRuntime`, and GVR resource name is `agentruntimes`\n15: \n16: ### Requirement: AgentRuntime spec fields and kubebuilder rules\n17: The system SHALL define `AgentRuntimeSpec` with: `Ports` as `[]TargetPort` serialized under JSON key `targetPort`; required `Template` (`*SandboxTemplate`) under JSON key `podTemplate`; required `SessionTimeout` (`*metav1.Duration`) under `sessionTimeout` with kubebuilder default `\"15m\"`; required `MaxSessionDuration` (`*metav1.Duration`) under `maxSessionDuration` with kubebuilder default `\"8h\"`.\n18: \n19: #### Scenario: SandboxTemplate embeds Pod spec\n20: - **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntime` with `spec.podTemplate`\n21: - **WHEN** the template is deserialized\n22: - **THEN** `labels` and `annotations` are optional maps and `spec` is required and of type `corev1.PodSpec`\n23: \n24: ### Requirement: AgentRuntime status\n25: The system SHALL define `AgentRuntimeStatus` with optional `conditions` of type `[]metav1.Condition`.\n26: \n27: #### Scenario: Conditions optional\n28: - **GIVEN** a minimal `AgentRuntime` object\n29: - **WHEN** status is omitted or empty\n30: - **THEN** deserialization succeeds without requiring `conditions`\n31: \n32: ### Requirement: CodeInterpreter CRD schema\n33: The system SHALL expose a namespaced `CodeInterpreter` CRD in the same API group/version with subresource `status` and print column `Age` from `.metadata.creationTimestamp`.\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreter GVR\n36: - **GIVEN** dynamic client configuration for workload templates\n37: - **WHEN** GVR is constructed for `codeinterpreters`\n38: - **THEN** group is `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`, version `v1alpha1`, resource `codeinterpreters`\n39: \n40: ### Requirement: CodeInterpreterSpec fields\n41: The system SHALL define `CodeInterpreterSpec` with: optional `Ports` (`[]TargetPort`, JSON `ports`); required `Template` (`*CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate`, JSON `template`); optional `SessionTimeout` with default `\"15m\"`; optional `MaxSessionDuration` with default `\"8h\"`; optional `WarmPoolSize` (`*int32`); optional `AuthMode` (`AuthModeType`, JSON `authMode`) with default `\"picod\"` and enum `picod` or `none`.\n42: \n43: #### Scenario: Auth mode constants\n44: - **GIVEN** API constants for auth mode\n45: - **WHEN** `AuthMode` is compared\n46: - **THEN** `AuthModePicoD` equals `\"picod\"` and `AuthModeNone` equals `\"none\"`\n47: \n48: ### Requirement: CodeInterpreterStatus fields\n49: The system SHALL define `CodeInterpreterStatus` with optional `conditions` and optional boolean `ready`.\n50: \n51: #### Scenario: Ready flag\n52: - **GIVEN** a reconciled `CodeInterpreter`\n53: - **WHEN** status is updated by the controller\n54: - **THEN** `status.ready` may be set to `true` alongside a `Ready` condition\n55: \n56: ### Requirement: TargetPort and Protocol types\n57: The system SHALL define `TargetPort` with optional `pathPrefix`, optional `name`, required `port` (`uint32`), and required `protocol` (`ProtocolType`) with kubebuilder default `HTTP` and enum `HTTP` or `HTTPS`.\n58: \n59: #### Scenario: Protocol constants\n60: - **GIVEN** port configuration without explicit protocol in some code paths\n61: - **WHEN** defaults apply at API level\n62: - **THEN** default protocol is `HTTP` per kubebuilder marker\n63: \n64: ### Requirement: Workload manager health endpoint\n65: The system SHALL serve `GET /health` without authentication and SHALL respond `200` with JSON body `{\"status\":\"healthy\"}`.\n66: \n67: #### Scenario: Health bypasses auth middleware\n68: - **GIVEN** `EnableAuth` is true\n69: - **WHEN** a client calls `GET /health` with no `Authorization` header\n70: - **THEN** the response status is 200 and body contains `\"status\":\"healthy\"`\n71: \n72: ### Requirement: Workload manager v1 routes and middleware\n73: The system SHALL mount a `/v1` route group with `loggingMiddleware` then `authMiddleware` (order preserved), and SHALL register `POST /v1/agent-runtime`, `DELETE /v1/agent-runtime/sessions/:sessionId`, `POST /v1/code-interpreter`, and `DELETE /v1/code-interpreter/sessions/:sessionId`.\n74: \n75: #### Scenario: Session id path parameter\n76: - **GIVEN** a delete request\n77: - **WHEN** Gin binds the path\n78: - **THEN** the session identifier is read from parameter name `sessionId` (camelCase)\n79: \n80: ### Requirement: Create sandbox request validation\n81: The system SHALL accept JSON for create endpoints matching `CreateSandboxRequest` with fields `kind`, `name`, `namespace`; SHALL overwrite `kind` from the handler (`AgentRuntime` or `CodeInterpreter`); and SHALL reject requests where `kind` is not one of those, `namespace` is empty, or `name` is empty.\n82: \n83: #### Scenario: Validation failure returns 400\n84: - **GIVEN** the handler sets `sandboxReq.Kind` from the route and `Validate()` is called\n85: - **WHEN** `namespace` or `name` is empty in the JSON body\n86: - **THEN** the response is 400 and the error message includes `required` (e.g. `namespace is required` or `name is required`)\n87: \n88: ### Requirement: Create sandbox success response\n89: On successful creation the system SHALL respond `200` with `CreateSandboxResponse` containing `sessionId`, `sandboxId`, `sandboxName`, and `entryPoints` (each entry point has `path`, `protocol`, `endpoint`).\n90: \n91: #### Scenario: Entry points reflect TargetPort and pod IP\n92: - **GIVEN** a sandbox reaches running state and pod IP is resolved\n93: - **WHEN** the response is built\n94: - **THEN** each entry point `endpoint` is `host:port` joined from pod IP and configured port, with protocol string from `TargetPort.Protocol`\n95: \n96: ### Requirement: Create sandbox error responses\n97: The system SHALL return `400` with `{\"message\":...}` for invalid JSON or validation failure; `404` with message from wrapped not-found errors when AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter is missing from informer cache; `401` with message from client extraction error when `EnableAuth` is true; `500` with `{\"message\":\"internal server error\"}` for other create failures including timeout.\n98: \n99: #### Scenario: JSON parse failure\n100: - **GIVEN** a non-JSON body to `POST /v1/agent-runtime`\n101: - **WHEN** the handler binds JSON\n102: - **THEN** status is 400 and message is `Invalid request body`\n103: \n104: ### Requirement: Optional Bearer authentication via TokenReview\n105: When `EnableAuth` is true, the system SHALL require header `Authorization: Bearer <token>` with exactly two space-separated fields; SHALL validate via `authentication/v1` `TokenReview` create; SHALL cache results in an LRU cache (capacity 1000, entry TTL 5 minutes); and SHALL store in context: token, full username, service account name, namespace parsed from `system:serviceaccount:<ns>:<name>`.\n106: \n107: #### Scenario: Missing header\n108: - **GIVEN** `EnableAuth` is true\n109: - **WHEN** `/v1/...` is called without `Authorization`\n110: - **THEN** response is 401 with message `Missing authorization header` and handler chain aborts\n111: \n112: #### Scenario: TokenReview success path\n113: - **GIVEN** a valid service account token and `EnableAuth` true\n114: - **WHEN** `validateServiceAccountToken` runs with cache miss\n115: - **THEN** the server creates `TokenReview` with `spec.token` set and uses `status.user.username` when `status.authenticated` is true\n116: \n117: ### Requirement: Authenticated Kubernetes operations use user client\n118: When `EnableAuth` is true, the system SHALL use a per-user dynamic client (from bearer token) for creating/deleting `Sandbox` or `SandboxClaim` resources; when false, SHALL use the manager’s in-cluster/default dynamic client.\n119: \n120: #### Scenario: User client cache key\n121: - **GIVEN** repeated requests from the same namespace and service account name\n122: - **WHEN** `GetOrCreateUserK8sClient` is used\n123: - **THEN** the cache key is `<namespace>:<serviceAccountName>`\n124: \n125: ### Requirement: Sandbox creation ordering and store placeholder\n126: The system SHALL call `StoreSandbox` with a placeholder `SandboxInfo` before creating the `Sandbox` or `SandboxClaim` in the API; SHALL register a one-shot watcher before create; SHALL wait up to 2 minutes for sandbox status `running` from the reconciler; SHALL resolve pod IP and then `UpdateSandbox` with full info; and SHALL roll back the created CR on failure after the wait (delete Sandbox or SandboxClaim within a 30s timeout context).\n127: \n128: #### Scenario: Watcher registration before create\n129: - **GIVEN** a create request reaches `createSandbox`\n130: - **WHEN** the Sandbox CR is created\n131: - **THEN** `WatchSandboxOnce` was already invoked for that namespace/name\n132: \n133: #### Scenario: Timeout returns error\n134: - **GIVEN** no running notification within 2 minutes\n135: - **WHEN** the select completes\n136: - **THEN** creation fails with error `sandbox creation timed out` and HTTP 500 is returned to the client\n137: \n138: ### Requirement: Pod IP resolution\n139: The system SHALL prefer pod name equal to sandbox name; if annotation `agents.x-k8s.io/sandbox-pod-name` exists on the created Sandbox (from agent-sandbox controller), SHALL use that as pod name; SHALL load pod from informer cache and require `PodRunning` and non-empty `PodIP`; otherwise SHALL list pods by label `runtime.agentcube.io/sandbox-name=<sandboxName>` and pick the pod whose controller owner reference is kind `Sandbox` and name matches.\n140: \n141: #### Scenario: Pod not running yields error\n142: - **GIVEN** a matching pod in non-Running phase\n143: - **WHEN** IP is resolved\n144: - **THEN** resolution fails with an error indicating the pod is not running\n145: \n146: ### Requirement: Delete sandbox by session\n147: The system SHALL load session from store by `sessionId`; on `ErrNotFound` return `404` with message `Session ID <id> not found, maybe already deleted`; delete `SandboxClaim` when stored `Kind` is `SandboxClaim`, else delete `Sandbox`; treat API `NotFound` on delete as success; then `DeleteSandboxBySessionID`; success response `200` `{\"message\":\"Sandbox deleted successfully\"}`.\n148: \n149: #### Scenario: Store miss\n150: - **GIVEN** no session key in store\n151: - **WHEN** DELETE is invoked\n152: - **THEN** HTTP status is 404 and message mentions the session id\n153: \n154: ### Requirement: Garbage collection loop\n155: The system SHALL run a background goroutine tick every 15 seconds; each tick SHALL use a context timeout of 2 minutes; SHALL query inactive sessions with cutoff `now - 15m` and batch limit 16; SHALL query expired sessions with `before = now` and batch limit 16; SHALL merge lists and delete each unique workload then remove store entry by session ID.\n156: \n157: #### Scenario: GC uses DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout\n158: - **GIVEN** GC lists inactive sandboxes\n159: - **WHEN** computing the inactive cutoff\n160: - **THEN** `inactiveTime` equals `time.Now().Add(-DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout)` where `DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout` is 15 minutes\n161: \n162: ### Requirement: HTTP server and process behavior\n163: The system SHALL use Gin with `gin.New()` for the workload API; SHALL serve with `h2c` wrapping and `http2.Server`; SHALL use `ReadTimeout` 15s and `IdleTimeout` 90s for HTTP when not using TLS; SHALL ping the store before listening; SHALL sync informers (AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter, Pod) with up to 1 minute wait; on SIGINT/SIGTERM SHALL shutdown HTTP within 15s, cancel context, wait for background workers, then `Close()` the store.\n164: \n165: #### Scenario: TLS requires cert and key\n166: - **GIVEN** `EnableTLS` is true and cert or key path is empty\n167: - **WHEN** `Start` runs\n168: - **THEN** it returns an error that TLS is enabled but cert/key not provided\n169: \n170: ### Requirement: API error helper constants\n171: The system SHALL define in package `api` the sentinel errors `ErrAgentRuntimeNotFound`, `ErrCodeInterpreterNotFound`, `ErrTemplateMissing`, `ErrPublicKeyMissing`, and SHALL map `CodeInterpreter` kind to group-resource `agentcube.volcano.sh/codeinterpreters` and default kinds to `agentcube.volcano.sh/agentruntimes` for `NewSandboxTemplateNotFoundError`.\n172: \n173: #### Scenario: Session not found uses API machinery\n174: - **GIVEN** `NewSessionNotFoundError(\"sid\")`\n175: - **WHEN** the error is inspected as `APIStatus`\n176: - **THEN** the group resource is `agentcube.volcano.sh, Resource=sessions` and name is the session id\n\n(End of file - total 176 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Sandbox Orchestration Specification\n\n## Purpose\nOrchestrate agent sandboxes via Kubernetes CRDs (AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter), a Gin HTTP API (workload manager), session persistence, garbage collection, and optional service-account authentication.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: AgentRuntime CRD schema and API registration\nThe system SHALL expose a namespaced `AgentRuntime` custom resource in API group `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`, version `v1alpha1`, with subresource `status`, print column `Age` from `.metadata.creationTimestamp`, and SHALL register list kind `AgentRuntimeList`.\n\n#### Scenario: Group version and resource naming\n- **GIVEN** a Kubernetes API client resolving the CRD\n- **WHEN** the group, version, and kind are read from type metadata\n- **THEN** `GroupVersion` is `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`, kind `AgentRuntime`, and GVR resource name is `agentruntimes`\n\n### Requirement: AgentRuntime spec fields and kubebuilder rules\nThe system SHALL define `AgentRuntimeSpec` with: `Ports` as `[]TargetPort` serialized under JSON key `targetPort`; required `Template` (`*SandboxTemplate`) under JSON key `podTemplate`; required `SessionTimeout` (`*metav1.Duration`) under `sessionTimeout` with kubebuilder default `\"15m\"`; required `MaxSessionDuration` (`*metav1.Duration`) under `maxSessionDuration` with kubebuilder default `\"8h\"`.\n\n#### Scenario: SandboxTemplate embeds Pod spec\n- **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntime` with `spec.podTemplate`","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/sandbox-orchestration/spec.md","time":{"start":1775901387385,"end":1775901387393}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775901387397,"sessionID":"ses_284083eaaffeJGoSkdYn83qwvG","part":{"id":"prt_d7bf8a6bf001GZM9yLsF9JXmVZ","messageID":"msg_d7bf897ca001MxDpl2Thc7Hwtu","sessionID":"ses_284083eaaffeJGoSkdYn83qwvG","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-9c480e8425cd4424971c9b2f78c7f113","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/Makefile"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/Makefile</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: SHELL ?= /usr/bin/env bash -o pipefail\n2: \n3: ##@ General\n4: \n5: IMAGE_REPO ?= ghcr.io/volcano-sh/agentcube\n6: VERSION ?= $(shell git describe --tags --always --dirty 2>/dev/null || echo \"latest\")\n7: TARGETOS ?= linux\n8: TARGETARCH ?= amd64\n9: BINDIR ?= bin/\n10: GO_VERSION ?= 1.24\n11: GOLANGCI_LINT_VERSION ?= 1.64.7\n12: CONTROLLER_TOOLS_VERSION ?= v0.17.2\n13: INSTALL_PREFIX ?= $(shell go env GOPATH)/bin\n14: \n15: LOCALBIN ?= $(shell pwd)/bin\n16: CONTROLLER_GEN ?= $(LOCALBIN)/controller-gen\n17: GOLANGCI_LINT ?= $(LOCALBIN)/golangci-lint\n18: \n19: E2E_CLUSTER_NAME ?= agentcube-e2e\n20: AGENT_SANDBOX_VERSION ?= latest\n21: \n22: HUB ?= ghcr.io/volcano-sh\n23: WORKLOAD_MANAGER_IMAGE ?= workloadmanager:$(VERSION)\n24: ROUTER_IMAGE ?= agentcube-router:$(VERSION)\n25: PICOD_IMAGE ?= picod:$(VERSION)\n26: IMAGE_REGISTRY ?= \"\"\n27: \n28: define go-install-tool\n29: @[ -f \"$(1)\" ] || { \\\n30: set -e ; \\\n31: echo \"Installing $(2)\" ; \\\n32: GOBIN=$(LOCALBIN) go install $(2)@$(3) ; }\n33: endef\n34: \n35: .PHONY: all build build-workloadmanager build-router build-picod build-agentd \\\n36:         build-agentctl build-agentcube build-agentsandbox build-all \\\n37:         build-linux-amd64 build-linux-arm64 build-darwin-amd64 build-darwin-arm64\n38: \n39: ##@ Build\n40: \n41: all: build\n42: \n43: build: generate ## Build all binaries\n44: \tgo build -o bin/workloadmanager ./cmd/workload-manager\n45: \tgo build -o bin/router ./cmd/router\n46: \tgo build -o bin/picod ./cmd/picod\n47: \tgo build -o bin/agentd ./cmd/agentd\n48: \tgo build -o bin/agentctl ./cmd/agentctl\n49: \tgo build -o bin/agentcube ./cmd/agentcube\n50: \tgo build -o bin/agentsandbox ./cmd/agentsandbox\n51: \n52: build-workloadmanager: generate ## Build workloadmanager binary only\n53: \tgo build -o bin/workloadmanager ./cmd/workload-manager\n54: \n55: build-router: generate ## Build router binary only\n56: \tgo build -o bin/router ./cmd/router\n57: \n58: build-picod: generate ## Build picod binary only\n59: \tgo build -o bin/picod ./cmd/picod\n60: \n61: build-agentd: generate ## Build agentd binary only\n62: \tgo build -o bin/agentd ./cmd/agentd\n63: \n64: build-agentctl: generate ## Build agentctl binary only\n65: \tgo build -o bin/agentctl ./cmd/agentctl\n66: \n67: build-agentcube: generate ## Build agentcube binary only\n68: \tgo build -o bin/agentcube ./cmd/agentcube\n69: \n70: build-agentsandbox: generate ## Build agentsandbox binary only\n71: \tgo build -o bin/agentsandbox ./cmd/agentsandbox\n72: \n73: build-all: build-workloadmanager build-router build-picod build-agentd \\\n74:            build-agentctl build-agentcube build-agentsandbox ## Build all binaries individually\n75: \n76: build-linux-amd64: generate ## Build for Linux AMD64\n77: \tGOOS=linux GOARCH=amd64 go build -o bin/workloadmanager ./cmd/workload-manager\n78: \tGOOS=linux GOARCH=amd64 go build -o bin/router ./cmd/router\n79: \tGOOS=linux GOARCH=amd64 go build -o bin/picod ./cmd/picod\n80: \tGOOS=linux GOARCH=amd64 go build -o bin/agentd ./cmd/agentd\n81: \tGOOS=linux GOARCH=amd64 go build -o bin/agentctl ./cmd/agentctl\n82: \tGOOS=linux GOARCH=amd64 go build -o bin/agentcube ./cmd/agentcube\n83: \tGOOS=linux GOARCH=amd64 go build -o bin/agentsandbox ./cmd/agentsandbox\n84: \n85: build-linux-arm64: generate ## Build for Linux ARM64\n86: \tGOOS=linux GOARCH=arm64 go build -o bin/workloadmanager ./cmd/workload-manager\n87: \tGOOS=linux GOARCH=arm64 go build -o bin/router ./cmd/router\n88: \tGOOS=linux GOARCH=arm64 go build -o bin/picod ./cmd/picod\n89: \tGOOS=linux GOARCH=arm64 go build -o bin/agentd ./cmd/agentd\n90: \tGOOS=linux GOARCH=arm64 go build -o bin/agentctl ./cmd/agentctl\n91: \tGOOS=linux GOARCH=arm64 go build -o bin/agentcube ./cmd/agentcube\n92: \tGOOS=linux GOARCH=arm64 go build -o bin/agentsandbox ./cmd/agentsandbox\n93: \n94: build-darwin-amd64: generate ## Build for Darwin AMD64\n95: \tGOOS=darwin GOARCH=amd64 go build -o bin/workloadmanager ./cmd/workload-manager\n96: \tGOOS=darwin GOARCH=amd64 go build -o bin/router ./cmd/router\n97: \tGOOS=darwin GOARCH=amd64 go build -o bin/picod ./cmd/picod\n98: \tGOOS=darwin GOARCH=amd64 go build -o bin/agentd ./cmd/agentd\n99: \tGOOS=darwin GOARCH=amd64 go build -o bin/agentctl ./cmd/agentctl\n100: \tGOOS=darwin GOARCH=amd64 go build -o bin/agentcube ./cmd/agentcube\n101: \tGOOS=darwin GOARCH=amd64 go build -o bin/agentsandbox ./cmd/agentsandbox\n102: \n103: build-darwin-arm64: generate ## Build for Darwin ARM64\n104: \tGOOS=darwin GOARCH=arm64 go build -o bin/workloadmanager ./cmd/workload-manager\n105: \tGOOS=darwin GOARCH=arm64 go build -o bin/router ./cmd/router\n106: \tGOOS=darwin GOARCH=arm64 go build -o bin/picod ./cmd/picod\n107: \tGOOS=darwin GOARCH=arm64 go build -o bin/agentd ./cmd/agentd\n108: \tGOOS=darwin GOARCH=arm64 go build -o bin/agentctl ./cmd/agentctl\n109: \tGOOS=darwin GOARCH=arm64 go build -o bin/agentcube ./cmd/agentcube\n110: \tGOOS=darwin GOARCH=arm64 go build -o bin/agentsandbox ./cmd/agentsandbox\n111: \n112: .PHONY: test test-coverage test-race\n113: \n114: ##@ Test\n115: \n116: test: ## Run unit tests with verbose output\n117: \tgo test -v ./...\n118: \n119: test-coverage: ## Run tests with coverage report\n120: \tgo test -coverprofile=coverage.out ./...\n121: \tgo tool cover -func=coverage.out\n122: \tgo tool cover -html=coverage.out -o coverage.html\n123: \n124: test-race: ## Run tests with race detector\n125: \tgo test -race ./...\n126: \n127: .PHONY: fmt vet lint golangci-lint gen-check gen-copyright\n128: \n129: ##@ Quality\n130: \n131: fmt: ## Format Go files\n132: \tgo fmt ./...\n133: \n134: vet: ## Run go vet\n135: \tgo vet ./...\n136: \n137: lint: golangci-lint ## Run golangci-lint\n138: \t$(GOLANGCI_LINT) run ./...\n139: \n140: golangci-lint:\n141: \t$(call go-install-tool,$(GOLANGCI_LINT),github.com/golangci/golangci-lint/cmd/golangci-lint,$(GOLANGCI_LINT_VERSION))\n142: \n143: gen-check: gen-all ## Verify generated code is up to date\n144: \tgit diff --exit-code\n145: \n146: gen-copyright: ## Generate copyright headers\n147: \thack/update-copyright.sh\n148: \n149: .PHONY: generate controller-gen gen-crd gen-client gen-all\n150: \n151: ##@ Codegen\n152: \n153: generate: controller-gen ## Generate deepcopy and object code\n154: \t$(CONTROLLER_GEN) object:headerFile=\"hack/boilerplate.go.txt\" paths=\"./pkg/apis/...\"\n155: \n156: controller-gen:\n157: \t$(call go-install-tool,$(CONTROLLER_GEN),sigs.k8s.io/controller-tools/cmd/controller-gen,$(CONTROLLER_TOOLS_VERSION))\n158: \n159: gen-crd: controller-gen ## Generate CRD manifests\n160: \t$(CONTROLLER_GEN) crd paths=\"./pkg/apis/...\" output:crd:artifacts:config=manifests/crds\n161: \n162: gen-client: ## Generate client-go code\n163: \thack/update-codegen.sh\n164: \n165: gen-all: generate gen-client ## Run all code generation\n166: \n167: .PHONY: docker-build docker-build-router docker-build-picod docker-build-all \\\n168:         docker-buildx-push docker-buildx-push-router docker-buildx-push-picod \\\n169:         docker-push docker-push-router docker-push-picod\n170: \n171: .NOTPARALLEL: docker-build-all\n172: \n173: ##@ Docker\n174: \n175: docker-build: ## Build workloadmanager Docker image\n176: \tdocker build \\\n177: \t\t-f docker/Dockerfile \\\n178: \t\t-t $(IMAGE_REPO)/workloadmanager:$(VERSION) \\\n179: \t\t--build-arg TARGETOS=$(TARGETOS) \\\n180: \t\t--build-arg TARGETARCH=$(TARGETARCH) \\\n181: \t\t.\n182: \n183: docker-build-router: ## Build router Docker image\n184: \tdocker build \\\n185: \t\t-f docker/Dockerfile.router \\\n186: \t\t-t $(IMAGE_REPO)/router:$(VERSION) \\\n187: \t\t--build-arg TARGETOS=$(TARGETOS) \\\n188: \t\t--build-arg TARGETARCH=$(TARGETARCH) \\\n189: \t\t.\n190: \n191: docker-build-picod: ## Build picod Docker image\n192: \tdocker build \\\n193: \t\t-f docker/Dockerfile.picod \\\n194: \t\t-t $(IMAGE_REPO)/picod:$(VERSION) \\\n195: \t\t.\n196: \n197: docker-build-all: docker-build docker-build-router docker-build-picod ## Build all Docker images\n198: \n199: docker-buildx-push: ## Build and push workloadmanager multi-arch image\n200: \tdocker buildx build \\\n201: \t\t-f docker/Dockerfile \\\n202: \t\t--platform linux/amd64,linux/arm64 \\\n203: \t\t--build-arg TARGETOS=linux \\\n204: \t\t--build-arg TARGETARCH=amd64 \\\n205: \t\t--push \\\n206: \t\t-t $(IMAGE_REPO)/workloadmanager:$(VERSION) \\\n207: \t\t.\n208: \n209: docker-buildx-push-router: ## Build and push router multi-arch image\n210: \tdocker buildx build \\\n211: \t\t-f docker/Dockerfile.router \\\n212: \t\t--platform linux/amd64,linux/arm64 \\\n213: \t\t--push \\\n214: \t\t-t $(IMAGE_REPO)/router:$(VERSION) \\\n215: \t\t.\n216: \n217: docker-buildx-push-picod: ## Build and push picod multi-arch image\n218: \tdocker buildx build \\\n219: \t\t-f docker/Dockerfile.picod \\\n220: \t\t--platform linux/amd64,linux/arm64 \\\n221: \t\t--push \\\n222: \t\t-t $(IMAGE_REPO)/picod:$(VERSION) \\\n223: \t\t.\n224: \n225: docker-push: ## Push workloadmanager image to registry\n226: \tdocker push $(IMAGE_REPO)/workloadmanager:$(VERSION)\n227: \n228: docker-push-router: ## Push router image to registry\n229: \tdocker push $(IMAGE_REPO)/router:$(VERSION)\n230: \n231: docker-push-picod: ## Push picod image to registry\n232: \tdocker push $(IMAGE_REPO)/picod:$(VERSION)\n233: \n234: .PHONY: kind-load kind-load-router kind-load-picod kind-load-all\n235: \n236: ##@ Kind\n237: \n238: kind-load: docker-build ## Load workloadmanager image into Kind cluster\n239: \tkind load docker-image $(IMAGE_REPO)/workloadmanager:$(VERSION) --name $(E2E_CLUSTER_NAME)\n240: \n241: kind-load-router: docker-build-router ## Load router image into Kind cluster\n242: \tkind load docker-image $(IMAGE_REPO)/router:$(VERSION) --name $(E2E_CLUSTER_NAME)\n243: \n244: kind-load-picod: docker-build-picod ## Load picod image into Kind cluster\n245: \tkind load docker-image $(IMAGE_REPO)/picod:$(VERSION) --name $(E2E_CLUSTER_NAME)\n246: \n247: kind-load-all: kind-load kind-load-router kind-load-picod ## Load all images into Kind cluster\n248: \n249: .PHONY: e2e e2e-setup e2e-clean\n250: \n251: ##@ E2E\n252: \n253: e2e: ## Run E2E tests\n254: \t./test/e2e/run_e2e.sh\n255: \n256: e2e-setup: ## Setup E2E test environment\n257: \tkind create cluster --name $(E2E_CLUSTER_NAME) --config test/e2e/kind-config.yaml\n258: \n259: e2e-clean: ## Clean up E2E test resources\n260: \tkind delete cluster --name $(E2E_CLUSTER_NAME) || true\n261: \trm -rf /tmp/agent-sandbox\n262: \n263: .PHONY: install install-workloadmanager install-router install-picod \\\n264:         install-agentd install-agentctl install-agentcube install-agentsandbox\n265: \n266: ##@ Install\n267: \n268: install: build ## Install all binaries to INSTALL_PREFIX\n269: \tmkdir -p $(INSTALL_PREFIX)\n270: \tcp bin/workloadmanager $(INSTALL_PREFIX)/\n271: \tcp bin/router $(INSTALL_PREFIX)/\n272: \tcp bin/picod $(INSTALL_PREFIX)/\n273: \tcp bin/agentd $(INSTALL_PREFIX)/\n274: \tcp bin/agentctl $(INSTALL_PREFIX)/\n275: \tcp bin/agentcube $(INSTALL_PREFIX)/\n276: \tcp bin/agentsandbox $(INSTALL_PREFIX)/\n277: \n278: install-workloadmanager: build-workloadmanager ## Install workloadmanager binary\n279: \tmkdir -p $(INSTALL_PREFIX)\n280: \tcp bin/workloadmanager $(INSTALL_PREFIX)/\n281: \n282: install-router: build-router ## Install router binary\n283: \tmkdir -p $(INSTALL_PREFIX)\n284: \tcp bin/router $(INSTALL_PREFIX)/\n285: \n286: install-picod: build-picod ## Install picod binary\n287: \tmkdir -p $(INSTALL_PREFIX)\n288: \tcp bin/picod $(INSTALL_PREFIX)/\n289: \n290: install-agentd: build-agentd ## Install agentd binary\n291: \tmkdir -p $(INSTALL_PREFIX)\n292: \tcp bin/agentd $(INSTALL_PREFIX)/\n293: \n294: install-agentctl: build-agentctl ## Install agentctl binary\n295: \tmkdir -p $(INSTALL_PREFIX)\n296: \tcp bin/agentctl $(INSTALL_PREFIX)/\n297: \n298: install-agentcube: build-agentcube ## Install agentcube binary\n299: \tmkdir -p $(INSTALL_PREFIX)\n300: \tcp bin/agentcube $(INSTALL_PREFIX)/\n301: \n302: install-agentsandbox: build-agentsandbox ## Install agentsandbox binary\n303: \tmkdir -p $(INSTALL_PREFIX)\n304: \tcp bin/agentsandbox $(INSTALL_PREFIX)/\n305: \n306: .PHONY: clean clean-bin clean-test\n307: \n308: ##@ Clean\n309: \n310: clean: clean-bin clean-test ## Remove all build artifacts\n311: \trm -f workloadmanager router picod agentd agentctl agentcube agentsandbox\n312: \n313: clean-bin: ## Remove binary directory\n314: \trm -rf bin/\n315: \n316: clean-test: ## Remove test artifacts\n317: \trm -f coverage.out coverage.html\n318: \n319: .PHONY: help\n320: \n321: ##@ Help\n322: \n323: help: ## Display this help screen\n324: \t@awk 'BEGIN {FS = \":.*##\"; printf \"\\nUsage:\\n  make <target>\\n\\n\"} \\\n325: \t\t/^##@/ { category = substr($$0, 4); printf \"%s\\n\", category } \\\n326: \t\t/^[%a-zA-Z0-9_-]+:.*##/ { \\\n327: \t\tprintf \"  %-30s %s\\n\", $$1, substr($$0, index($$0, \"##\") + 3) } \\\n328: \t\tEND { printf \"\\n\" }' $(MAKEFILE_LIST)\n\n(End of file - total 328 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"SHELL ?= /usr/bin/env bash -o pipefail\n\n##@ General\n\nIMAGE_REPO ?= ghcr.io/volcano-sh/agentcube\nVERSION ?= $(shell git describe --tags --always --dirty 2>/dev/null || echo \"latest\")\nTARGETOS ?= linux\nTARGETARCH ?= amd64\nBINDIR ?= bin/\nGO_VERSION ?= 1.24\nGOLANGCI_LINT_VERSION ?= 1.64.7\nCONTROLLER_TOOLS_VERSION ?= v0.17.2\nINSTALL_PREFIX ?= $(shell go env GOPATH)/bin\n\nLOCALBIN ?= $(shell pwd)/bin\nCONTROLLER_GEN ?= $(LOCALBIN)/controller-gen\nGOLANGCI_LINT ?= $(LOCALBIN)/golangci-lint\n\nE2E_CLUSTER_NAME ?= agentcube-e2e\nAGENT_SANDBOX_VERSION ?= latest","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/Makefile","time":{"start":1775901387383,"end":1775901387395}}}}
