{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775901403252,"sessionID":"ses_284083eaaffeJGoSkdYn83qwvG","part":{"id":"prt_d7bf8e49a0017VUv8X6IxQ1pjp","messageID":"msg_d7bf8aaad001jmI2oTrz1bEFwR","sessionID":"ses_284083eaaffeJGoSkdYn83qwvG","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-7e689f21f1c14c6f88707c6cf7885dc6","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/session-routing/spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/session-routing/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Session Routing Specification\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: Route HTTP invocation traffic to sandboxes by session: resolve or create sessions via the workload manager, track activity in the store, reverse-proxy to pod endpoints, and sign outbound requests with JWT when targeting sandboxes.\n5: \n6: ## Requirements\n7: \n8: ### Requirement: Session resolution and creation\n9: The system SHALL read session id from request header `x-agentcube-session-id`. When the header is empty, the system SHALL POST to the workload manager to create a sandbox. When non-empty, the system SHALL load `SandboxInfo` from the store by session id.\n10: \n11: #### Scenario: Missing session triggers workload manager create\n12: - **GIVEN** `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` is set and an invocation request has no `x-agentcube-session-id`\n13: - **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySession` runs for `AgentRuntimeKind`\n14: - **THEN** the client POSTs JSON `{\"kind\":\"AgentRuntime\",\"name\":...,\"namespace\":...}` to `{WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL}/v1/agent-runtime`\n15: \n16: #### Scenario: Unknown session returns not found\n17: - **GIVEN** a non-empty session id not present in store\n18: - **WHEN** the store returns `ErrNotFound`\n19: - **THEN** the error maps to `NewSessionNotFoundError(sessionID)` and the HTTP handler responds using API status (typically 404)\n20: \n21: ### Requirement: Workload manager URL and auth token for creates\n22: The system SHALL require environment variable `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` at session manager construction (non-empty). When the file `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` exists and is readable, the system SHALL attach `Authorization: Bearer <trimmed contents>` to create requests.\n23: \n24: #### Scenario: Missing WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL fails startup\n25: - **GIVEN** `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` is unset\n26: - **WHEN** `NewSessionManager` is called\n27: - **THEN** it returns error `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL environment variable is not set`\n28: \n29: ### Requirement: Create response validation\n30: The system SHALL accept workload manager HTTP 200 with body `CreateSandboxResponse`; SHALL reject with internal error if `sessionId` in body is empty; SHALL build in-memory `SandboxInfo` with `SandboxID`, `Name` (= `sandboxName`), `SessionID`, `EntryPoints` from the response (other fields may be zero).\n31: \n32: #### Scenario: Non-OK from workload manager\n33: - **GIVEN** workload manager returns HTTP 404\n34: - **WHEN** the session manager handles the response\n35: - **THEN** the error is `NewSandboxTemplateNotFoundError(namespace, name, kind)`\n36: \n37: ### Requirement: Reverse proxy to sandbox\n38: The system SHALL determine upstream URL from `SandboxInfo.EntryPoints` by first matching `path` prefix against the invocation path; if none match, SHALL use the first entry point. The system SHALL build URL by prefixing `protocol` (lowercase) and `://` to `endpoint` when protocol is set and endpoint lacks a scheme. The system SHALL use `httputil.NewSingleHostReverseProxy`, shared `http.Transport` on the proxy, and custom `Director` to set path, host, forwarding headers, and optional JWT.\n39: \n40: #### Scenario: No entry points\n41: - **GIVEN** `EntryPoints` is empty\n42: - **WHEN** upstream is determined\n43: - **THEN** the handler responds 404 JSON `{\"error\":\"no entry point found for sandbox\"}`\n44: \n45: ### Requirement: JWT injection for sandbox kinds\n46: For sandbox kinds `Sandbox` and `SandboxClaim`, the system SHALL generate a JWT before proxying and SHALL set `Authorization: Bearer <token>` on the proxied request.\n47: \n48: #### Scenario: Signing failure\n49: - **GIVEN** JWT generation returns an error\n50: - **WHEN** forwarding is attempted\n51: - **THEN** the handler responds 500 with JSON containing `\"code\":\"JWT_SIGNING_FAILED\"` and `\"error\":\"failed to sign request\"`\n52: \n53: ### Requirement: Forwarding headers and response header\n54: The system SHALL set `X-Forwarded-Host` from the incoming request host, `X-Forwarded-Proto` to `https` when TLS is present else `http`, and `X-Forwarded-For` by appending client IP to any existing values. The system SHALL set response header `x-agentcube-session-id` to the resolved session id on all proxied responses.\n55: \n56: #### Scenario: Path normalization\n57: - **GIVEN** the Gin path param is non-empty and lacks a leading slash\n58: - **WHEN** the director runs\n59: - **THEN** the outbound path is prefixed with `/`\n60: \n61: ### Requirement: Proxy error mapping\n62: The system SHALL map proxy errors containing `connection refused` to 502 `{\"error\":\"sandbox unreachable\"}`, containing `timeout` to 504 `{\"error\":\"sandbox timeout\"}`, and other errors to 502 `{\"error\":\"sandbox unreachable\"}`.\n63: \n64: #### Scenario: Downstream connection refused\n65: - **GIVEN** the reverse proxy fails with an error whose message includes `connection refused`\n66: - **WHEN** `ErrorHandler` runs\n67: - **THEN** status is 502 and error text is `sandbox unreachable`\n68: \n69: ### Requirement: Last-activity updates\n70: The system SHALL call `UpdateSessionLastActivity` with `time.Now()` after successfully resolving the sandbox and again after `forwardToSandbox` returns (twice per successful invoke path). Failures SHALL be logged as warnings only.\n71: \n72: #### Scenario: Store update failure does not block proxy\n73: - **GIVEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity` returns an error\n74: - **WHEN** handling continues\n75: - **THEN** the proxy still runs if sandbox resolution succeeded\n76: \n77: ### Requirement: Health endpoints\n78: The system SHALL expose `GET /health/live` returning 200 `{\"status\":\"alive\"}`. The system SHALL expose `GET /health/ready` returning 200 `{\"status\":\"ready\"}` when session manager is non-nil, else 503 with `status` and `error` fields.\n79: \n80: #### Scenario: Ready depends on session manager\n81: - **GIVEN** `sessionManager` is nil\n82: - **WHEN** `GET /health/ready` is served\n83: - **THEN** status is 503 and body includes `\"error\":\"session manager not available\"`\n84: \n85: ### Requirement: Concurrency limiting\n86: The system SHALL apply a semaphore middleware to `/v1/*` routes with capacity `MaxConcurrentRequests` (default 1000 when config value ≤ 0). When no slot is available, the system SHALL respond 429 JSON `{\"error\":\"server overloaded, please try again later\",\"code\":\"SERVER_OVERLOADED\"}` and abort.\n87: \n88: #### Scenario: Default limit when zero in config\n89: - **GIVEN** `NewServer` receives `MaxConcurrentRequests` 0\n90: - **WHEN** the server is constructed\n91: - **THEN** the effective limit is set to 1000 before route registration\n92: \n93: ### Requirement: Invocation route surface\n94: The system SHALL register GET and POST for `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/agent-runtimes/:name/invocations/*path` and for `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/code-interpreters/:name/invocations/*path`, with Gin logger, recovery, and concurrency middleware on the `/v1` group only.\n95: \n96: #### Scenario: Kind passed to session lookup\n97: - **GIVEN** agent-runtime invocation\n98: - **WHEN** `handleInvoke` runs\n99: - **THEN** kind argument is `AgentRuntime` (`types.AgentRuntimeKind`)\n100: \n101: ### Requirement: HTTP server behavior\n102: The system SHALL serve with `h2c` and `http2.Server`, `ReadTimeout` 30s, `IdleTimeout` 90s; on context cancel SHALL shutdown within 10s. Optional TLS SHALL require both cert and key paths.\n103: \n104: #### Scenario: TLS misconfiguration\n105: - **GIVEN** `EnableTLS` true and empty cert path\n106: - **WHEN** `Start` runs\n107: - **THEN** it returns error stating cert/key not provided\n108: \n109: ### Requirement: Identity secret bootstrap for JWT\n110: On server creation the system SHALL construct `JWTManager`, call `TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret`, and fail server creation if that returns error (except in-cluster skip path returns nil when not in cluster).\n111: \n112: #### Scenario: In-cluster secret creation\n113: - **GIVEN** in-cluster config succeeds and secret does not exist\n114: - **WHEN** `TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret` runs\n115: - **THEN** it creates opaque secret `picod-router-identity` in namespace from `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` or `default` with keys `private.pem` and `public.pem`\n\n(End of file - total 115 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Session Routing Specification\n\n## Purpose\nRoute HTTP invocation traffic to sandboxes by session: resolve or create sessions via the workload manager, track activity in the store, reverse-proxy to pod endpoints, and sign outbound requests with JWT when targeting sandboxes.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Session resolution and creation\nThe system SHALL read session id from request header `x-agentcube-session-id`. When the header is empty, the system SHALL POST to the workload manager to create a sandbox. When non-empty, the system SHALL load `SandboxInfo` from the store by session id.\n\n#### Scenario: Missing session triggers workload manager create\n- **GIVEN** `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` is set and an invocation request has no `x-agentcube-session-id`\n- **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySession` runs for `AgentRuntimeKind`\n- **THEN** the client POSTs JSON `{\"kind\":\"AgentRuntime\",\"name\":...,\"namespace\":...}` to `{WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL}/v1/agent-runtime`\n\n#### Scenario: Unknown session returns not found\n- **GIVEN** a non-empty session id not present in store\n- **WHEN** the store returns `ErrNotFound`\n- **THEN** the error maps to `NewSessionNotFoundError(sessionID)` and the HTTP handler responds using API status (typically 404)\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/session-routing/spec.md","time":{"start":1775901403240,"end":1775901403250}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775901403254,"sessionID":"ses_284083eaaffeJGoSkdYn83qwvG","part":{"id":"prt_d7bf8e823001R1hC47YZcZF4IT","messageID":"msg_d7bf8aaad001jmI2oTrz1bEFwR","sessionID":"ses_284083eaaffeJGoSkdYn83qwvG","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-4bb0a2f02d754f66a8e99e5cda9a1bf7","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/python-sdk/spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/python-sdk/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AgentCube Python SDK Specification\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: Python client library (`agentcube-sdk`) for creating Code Interpreter sessions via the Workload Manager (control plane) and executing code/files via the Router (data plane), plus invoking AgentRuntime workloads through the Router.\n6: \n7: ## Requirements\n8: \n9: ### Requirement: `CodeInterpreterClient` lifecycle\n10: The system SHALL construct a client that either reuses `session_id` or creates a session via `ControlPlaneClient.create_session`, then initializes `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` with header `x-agentcube-session-id`.\n11: \n12: #### Scenario: Context manager cleanup\n13: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient` is used as a context manager\n14: - **WHEN** the block exits (with or without exception)\n15: - **THEN** `__exit__` SHALL call `stop()`, which closes the data-plane session, deletes the control-plane session if `session_id` was set, and closes the control plane HTTP session\n16: \n17: #### Scenario: Data plane init failure after session create\n18: - **GIVEN** `session_id` was not provided and `create_session` succeeded\n19: - **WHEN** `_init_data_plane()` raises\n20: - **THEN** the client SHALL log a warning, call `delete_session(session_id)`, set `session_id` to `None`, and re-raise\n21: \n22: #### Scenario: Router URL required\n23: - **GIVEN** neither `router_url` nor environment variable `ROUTER_URL` is set\n24: - **WHEN** `CodeInterpreterClient.__init__` runs\n25: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError` explaining that Router URL must be provided via argument or `ROUTER_URL`\n26: \n27: ### Requirement: Code Interpreter — execute, files, stop\n28: The system SHALL expose `execute_command`, `run_code`, `write_file`, `upload_file`, `download_file`, `list_files`, and `stop` delegating to the data plane client where applicable.\n29: \n30: #### Scenario: Command non-zero exit\n31: - **GIVEN** `execute_command` receives a response with `exit_code != 0`\n32: - **WHEN** the response JSON is parsed\n33: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `CommandExecutionError` with `exit_code`, `stderr`, and `command`\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: Python code execution path\n36: - **GIVEN** `language` is `python`, `py`, or `python3`\n37: - **WHEN** `run_code` runs\n38: - **THEN** the system SHALL write a timestamped `.py` file via `write_file` and execute `python3 <file>` through `execute_command`\n39: \n40: ### Requirement: `AgentRuntimeClient` lifecycle\n41: The system SHALL bootstrap or reuse `session_id` from the Agent Runtime invocation endpoint via `GET` on the base invocation URL, then `POST` JSON payloads with session header.\n42: \n43: #### Scenario: Context manager\n44: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is used as a context manager\n45: - **WHEN** the block exits\n46: - **THEN** `close()` SHALL close the underlying `requests.Session`\n47: \n48: #### Scenario: Bootstrap session id\n49: - **GIVEN** `session_id` is not provided\n50: - **WHEN** the client initializes\n51: - **THEN** it SHALL `GET` `{router}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/` and read header `x-agentcube-session-id`; if missing, raise `ValueError` with message `Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id`\n52: \n53: #### Scenario: Invoke without session\n54: - **GIVEN** `session_id` is falsy\n55: - **WHEN** `invoke` is called\n56: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError(\"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\")`\n57: \n58: ### Requirement: HTTP client contracts — control plane\n59: The system SHALL use `requests.Session` with connection pooling (`HTTPAdapter`) for Workload Manager calls.\n60: \n61: #### Scenario: Create session\n62: - **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient.create_session(name, namespace, metadata=None, ttl=3600)`\n63: - **WHEN** the request succeeds\n64: - **THEN** the client SHALL `POST {base_url}/v1/code-interpreter` with JSON body `{\"name\",\"namespace\",\"ttl\",\"metadata\"}` and return `data[\"sessionId\"]` or raise `ValueError` if absent\n65: \n66: #### Scenario: Delete session\n67: - **GIVEN** `delete_session(session_id)`\n68: - **WHEN** the server returns 404\n69: - **THEN** the method SHALL return `True`; on other failures it SHALL log and return `False`\n70: \n71: #### Scenario: Workload Manager URL and auth\n72: - **GIVEN** `workload_manager_url` and `auth_token` may be omitted\n73: - **WHEN** the client initializes\n74: - **THEN** `base_url` SHALL resolve from `workload_manager_url` or `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`; token SHALL resolve from `auth_token` or `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` via `read_token_from_file`, and if present set `Authorization: Bearer {token}`\n75: \n76: ### Requirement: HTTP client contracts — data plane (Code Interpreter)\n77: The system SHALL target Router-relative paths under `{base_url}` derived from `urljoin(router_url, \"/v1/namespaces/{ns}/code-interpreters/{cr_name}/invocations/\")` unless `base_url` is passed explicitly.\n78: \n79: #### Scenario: Execute command\n80: - **WHEN** `execute_command` posts to `api/execute`\n81: - **THEN** the body SHALL be JSON `{\"command\": [...], \"timeout\": \"<n>s\"}` and read timeout SHALL be `timeout_value + 2.0` seconds when numeric (to avoid `ReadTimeout` before PicoD returns exit 124)\n82: \n83: #### Scenario: Files API\n84: - **WHEN** `write_file` runs\n85: - **THEN** it SHALL `POST api/files` with base64 `content`, `path`, `mode` `\"0644\"`\n86: - **WHEN** `upload_file` runs\n87: - **THEN** it SHALL `POST` multipart to `api/files` with headers including `x-agentcube-session-id`\n88: \n89: ### Requirement: HTTP client contracts — data plane (Agent Runtime)\n90: The system SHALL `POST` JSON to the invocation base URL with headers `x-agentcube-session-id` and `Content-Type: application/json`.\n91: \n92: #### Scenario: Invoke timeout tuple\n93: - **GIVEN** `invoke(..., timeout=None)`\n94: - **WHEN** the request is sent\n95: - **THEN** `timeout` SHALL be `(connect_timeout, self.timeout)` where `self.timeout` defaults to `120`\n96: \n97: ### Requirement: Session header management\n98: The system SHALL use lowercase header name `x-agentcube-session-id` for SDK Router requests (`CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` default session header; `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` uses class constant `SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"`).\n99: \n100: #### Scenario: Code Interpreter session header\n101: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` is constructed\n102: - **WHEN** any `_request` or upload runs\n103: - **THEN** the session SHALL include `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}` (upload sets it explicitly on the multipart POST)\n104: \n105: ### Requirement: Exception hierarchy\n106: The system SHALL define `AgentCubeError`, `CommandExecutionError`, `SessionError`, and `DataPlaneError` in `agentcube.exceptions`.\n107: \n108: #### Scenario: Command failure\n109: - **GIVEN** remote command returns non-zero exit code in JSON\n110: - **WHEN** `execute_command` processes the response\n111: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `CommandExecutionError` (subclass of `AgentCubeError`)\n112: \n113: #### Scenario: SessionError / DataPlaneError usage\n114: - **GIVEN** the current package sources under `agentcube/`\n115: - **WHEN** searching for `raise SessionError` / `raise DataPlaneError`\n116: - **THEN** these classes are defined for extension but not raised by the core client modules in the extracted tree (callers MAY rely on `ValueError`, `requests` exceptions, or `CommandExecutionError`)\n117: \n118: ### Requirement: Timeout behavior\n119: The system SHALL default control-plane and data-plane read timeouts to `120` seconds and connect timeout to `5.0` seconds unless overridden per call.\n120: \n121: #### Scenario: Per-call override for code execution\n122: - **GIVEN** `execute_command(command, timeout=None)`\n123: - **WHEN** `timeout` is `None`\n124: - **THEN** the effective timeout value SHALL default to `self.timeout` (`120`) for constructing the PicoD timeout string and read-timeout buffer logic\n125: \n126: #### Scenario: AgentRuntimeClient constructor timeouts\n127: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient(..., timeout=120, connect_timeout=5.0)`\n128: - **WHEN** `invoke` is called without `timeout`\n129: - **THEN** read timeout SHALL be `120` (instance default)\n130: \n131: ---\n132: \n133: **Public package surface:** `agentcube/__init__.py` exports only `CodeInterpreterClient` and `AgentRuntimeClient` in `__all__`.\n\n(End of file - total 133 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AgentCube Python SDK Specification\n\n## Purpose\n\nPython client library (`agentcube-sdk`) for creating Code Interpreter sessions via the Workload Manager (control plane) and executing code/files via the Router (data plane), plus invoking AgentRuntime workloads through the Router.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: `CodeInterpreterClient` lifecycle\nThe system SHALL construct a client that either reuses `session_id` or creates a session via `ControlPlaneClient.create_session`, then initializes `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` with header `x-agentcube-session-id`.\n\n#### Scenario: Context manager cleanup\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient` is used as a context manager\n- **WHEN** the block exits (with or without exception)\n- **THEN** `__exit__` SHALL call `stop()`, which closes the data-plane session, deletes the control-plane session if `session_id` was set, and closes the control plane HTTP session\n\n#### Scenario: Data plane init failure after session create\n- **GIVEN** `session_id` was not provided and `create_session` succeeded\n- **WHEN** `_init_data_plane()` raises\n- **THEN** the client SHALL log a warning, call `delete_session(session_id)`, set `session_id` to `None`, and re-raise","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/python-sdk/spec.md","time":{"start":1775901403243,"end":1775901403252}}}}
